# Modus Icons Usage Guide for Angular Applications

## Overview

This guide provides comprehensive instructions for using Modus Icons in Angular applications with the Modus Web Components design system. Modus Icons use **icon font ligatures** with **underscore naming convention**.

## Setup and Configuration

### 1. Font Loading

**✅ CORRECT: Load via HTML `<link>` tag in `src/index.html`**

For complete icon support (outlined, solid, and default variants), use the local CSS file:

```html
<link rel="stylesheet" href="modus-icons.css" />
```

This loads all three font families:

- `modus-icons` - default/solid icons
- `modus-icons-outlined` - outlined variant icons
- `modus-icons-solid` - solid variant icons

**Alternative: CDN (limited to one variant)**

```html
<link
  rel="stylesheet"
  href="https://cdn.jsdelivr.net/npm/@trimble-oss/modus-icons@1.17.0/dist/field-systems/fonts/modus-icons.css"
/>
```

Note: The CDN version only includes the basic `modus-icons` font family.

**❌ INCORRECT: CSS @import (causes loading issues with Vite)**

```css
/* Don't use this - causes build warnings and loading issues */
@import url('https://cdn.jsdelivr.net/npm/@trimble-oss/modus-icons@1.17.0/dist/field-systems/fonts/modus-icons.css');
```

### 2. Icon Font Implementation

Modus Icons use **font ligatures** where the icon name becomes the text content of an element with the `modus-icons` class.

## Icon Naming Convention

**CRITICAL: Modus Icons use UNDERSCORES (\_), not hyphens (-)**

### ✅ CORRECT Icon Names

```html
<i class="modus-icons">save_disk</i>
<i class="modus-icons">arrow_left</i>
<i class="modus-icons">arrow_right</i>
<i class="modus-icons">add_circle</i>
<i class="modus-icons">user_permissions</i>
<i class="modus-icons">file_upload</i>
```

### ❌ INCORRECT Icon Names

```html
<!-- Don't use hyphens -->
<i class="modus-icons">save-disk</i>
<i class="modus-icons">arrow-left</i>
<i class="modus-icons">add-circle</i>
```

## Usage Patterns

### 1. Angular Component Integration

**In Modus Button Components:**

```html
<!-- Icon with text (left position) -->
<modus-button icon="save_disk" iconPosition="left">Save File</modus-button>

<!-- Icon with text (right position) -->
<modus-button icon="download" iconPosition="right">Download</modus-button>

<!-- Icon only (requires aria-label) -->
<modus-button icon="settings" iconPosition="only" ariaLabel="Open settings"></modus-button>
```

**Direct HTML Usage:**

```html
<!-- Decorative icon (not announced by screen readers) -->
<i class="modus-icons text-lg" aria-hidden="true">user_add</i>

<!-- Informational icon (announced by screen readers) -->
<i class="modus-icons text-base" role="img" aria-label="Settings">settings</i>
```

### 2. Sizing Icons

Use Tailwind text utilities mapped to Modus font sizes:

```html
<!-- Small icon -->
<i class="modus-icons text-sm">info</i>

<!-- Base icon (Modus default 14px) -->
<i class="modus-icons text-base">warning</i>

<!-- Large icon (16px) -->
<i class="modus-icons text-lg">error</i>

<!-- Extra large icon (18px) -->
<i class="modus-icons text-xl">success</i>
```

**Modus Font Size Scale for Icons:**

| Tailwind Class | Size | Usage                  | Example Context        |
| -------------- | ---- | ---------------------- | ---------------------- |
| `text-2xs`     | 8px  | Micro icons, badges    | Status indicators      |
| `text-xs`      | 10px | Small labels, captions | Form field icons       |
| `text-sm`      | 12px | Secondary icons        | Navigation icons       |
| `text-base`    | 14px | **Modus default size** | Standard UI icons      |
| `text-lg`      | 16px | Body text icons        | Button icons with text |
| `text-xl`      | 18px | Large icons            | Icon-only buttons      |
| `text-2xl`     | 20px | Prominent icons        | Section headers        |
| `text-3xl`     | 24px | Display icons          | Feature highlights     |
| `text-4xl`     | 30px | Hero icons             | Landing page elements  |

**Implementation Examples:**

```html
<!-- Micro icons for badges -->
<span class="inline-flex items-center gap-1">
  <i class="modus-icons text-2xs">star</i>
  <span class="text-xs">Premium</span>
</span>

<!-- Standard icons with text -->
<button class="flex items-center gap-2">
  <i class="modus-icons text-lg">save_disk</i>
  <span>Save File</span>
</button>

<!-- Large standalone icons -->
<i class="modus-icons text-3xl text-primary">check_circle</i>

<!-- Hero icons for landing pages -->
<i class="modus-icons text-4xl text-success">verified</i>

<!-- Custom sizes using inline styles (when needed) -->
<i class="modus-icons" style="font-size: 2rem; color: orange;">apps</i>
<i class="modus-icons" style="font-size: 48px;">dashboard</i>
```

**Custom Font Sizes:**

As noted in the [Modus Icons documentation](https://modus-icons.trimble.com/modus-solid/), you can use `font-size` and `color` properties directly for custom sizing:

```html
<!-- Using rem units -->
<i class="modus-icons" style="font-size: 2rem;">apps</i>

<!-- Using pixel values -->
<i class="modus-icons" style="font-size: 48px;">dashboard</i>

<!-- Using CSS custom properties -->
<i class="modus-icons" style="font-size: var(--custom-icon-size);">settings</i>
```

**Recommendation**: Prefer Tailwind utility classes (`text-lg`, `text-xl`, etc.) for consistency with the Modus design system. Use custom `font-size` only when you need sizes not available in the Modus scale.

## Button Icon Sizing

The `modus-button` component provides intelligent icon sizing that automatically adapts to button size, with the option for explicit control.

### Automatic Icon Sizing

Icons automatically scale based on button size and position:

```html
<!-- Icons scale with button size -->
<modus-button size="xs" icon="star" iconPosition="left">Extra Small</modus-button>
<modus-button size="sm" icon="star" iconPosition="left">Small</modus-button>
<modus-button size="md" icon="star" iconPosition="left">Medium</modus-button>
<modus-button size="lg" icon="star" iconPosition="left">Large</modus-button>

<!-- Icon-only buttons use larger icons -->
<modus-button size="xs" icon="settings" iconPosition="only" ariaLabel="Settings" />
<modus-button size="md" icon="settings" iconPosition="only" ariaLabel="Settings" />
<modus-button size="lg" icon="settings" iconPosition="only" ariaLabel="Settings" />
```

**Automatic Sizing Rules:**

| Button Size | Icons with Text  | Icon-Only Buttons  |
| ----------- | ---------------- | ------------------ |
| `xs`        | `text-xs` (10px) | `text-sm` (12px)   |
| `sm`        | `text-sm` (12px) | `text-base` (14px) |
| `md`        | `text-lg` (16px) | `text-xl` (18px)   |
| `lg`        | `text-xl` (18px) | `text-2xl` (20px)  |

### Explicit Icon Sizing

Override automatic sizing with the `iconSize` input:

```html
<!-- Custom icon sizes -->
<modus-button icon="star" iconSize="text-xs" iconPosition="left">Tiny Icon</modus-button>
<modus-button icon="star" iconSize="text-2xl" iconPosition="left">Large Icon</modus-button>

<!-- Mix button and icon sizes -->
<modus-button size="lg" icon="download" iconSize="text-sm" iconPosition="left">
  Large Button, Small Icon
</modus-button>
<modus-button size="sm" icon="download" iconSize="text-xl" iconPosition="left">
  Small Button, Large Icon
</modus-button>

<!-- Huge icon in icon-only button -->
<modus-button
  size="md"
  icon="check_circle"
  iconSize="text-3xl"
  iconPosition="only"
  ariaLabel="Success"
/>
```

### Best Practices

- **Use automatic sizing** for consistent, predictable icon scaling
- **Use explicit sizing** when you need specific visual emphasis or custom layouts
- **Icon-only buttons** automatically get larger icons for better touch targets
- **Maintain accessibility** by providing `ariaLabel` for icon-only buttons

