## Accessibility Guidelines

### 1. Decorative Icons

For purely decorative icons, use `aria-hidden="true"`:

```html
<button>
  <i class="modus-icons mr-2" aria-hidden="true">save_disk</i>
  Save Document
</button>
```

### 2. Informational Icons

For icons that convey meaning, provide proper labels:

```html
<!-- Using role="img" and aria-label -->
<i class="modus-icons" role="img" aria-label="Warning">warning</i>

<!-- Using aria-label on parent element -->
<button aria-label="Delete item">
  <i class="modus-icons" aria-hidden="true">delete</i>
</button>
```

### 3. Icon-Only Buttons

Always provide accessible labels for icon-only buttons:

```html
<modus-button icon="settings" iconPosition="only" ariaLabel="Open settings menu"></modus-button>
```

## Testing Icons

### 1. Visual Verification

Icons should display as actual glyphs, not text. If you see text like "save_disk" instead of a disk icon, check:

1. Font CSS is loaded correctly
2. Icon name uses underscores, not hyphens
3. `modus-icons` class is applied
4. Font has finished loading

### 2. Browser DevTools Check

```javascript
// Check if font is loaded
const testElement = document.createElement('span');
testElement.className = 'modus-icons';
document.body.appendChild(testElement);
const fontFamily = window.getComputedStyle(testElement).fontFamily;
console.log('Font loaded:', fontFamily.includes('modus-icons'));
document.body.removeChild(testElement);
```

### 3. Icon Name Validation

```javascript
// Test if an icon name works (should have width > 0)
const testIcon = (iconName) => {
  const element = document.createElement('i');
  element.className = 'modus-icons';
  element.textContent = iconName;
  element.style.position = 'absolute';
  element.style.left = '-9999px';
  document.body.appendChild(element);
  const width = element.getBoundingClientRect().width;
  document.body.removeChild(element);
  return width > 0;
};

console.log('save_disk works:', testIcon('save_disk'));
```

## Troubleshooting

### Problem: Icons show as text instead of glyphs

**Solutions:**

1. Verify font CSS is loaded in `index.html`
2. Check network tab for successful font file download
3. Ensure icon names use underscores (`save_disk` not `save-disk`)
4. Confirm `modus-icons` class is applied

### Problem: Some icons don't display

**Solutions:**

1. Verify icon name exists in Modus Icons library
2. Check spelling and underscore usage
3. Test icon name with validation script above

### Problem: Icons not accessible

**Solutions:**

1. Add `aria-hidden="true"` for decorative icons
2. Add `role="img"` and `aria-label` for informational icons
3. Provide `ariaLabel` prop for icon-only buttons

